<br>
As it is right now, when you borrow money from the treasury for trade skills, you have to repay 90% of the money. While I thought this was a good idea at first, it doesn't seem to be working. First off, to my knowledge, I'm the only one who has borrowed. And when I did, I saw why. I wasn't really able to get much skill with the 10 gold I borrowed, especially considering I had to pay back 9 gold. I ended up making that many times over just trying to get some skill moving. At low levels, 90% might work, but as the amounts get higher, more money raises less skill. <br>
<br>
I'd like to propose that the repayment percentage be changed from 90% to 50% of the original loan, repayable within 2 weeks. <br>
<br>
OR<br>
<br>
We can set aside a portion of the treasury that goes towards nothing but trade skills. The sponsored trade skill people can use this money to raise their skill, with no need to repay it. However, the amount of money set aside from the treasury can never go over 50% of the current treasury, and the money would be first come first serve. <br>
<br>
I want to hear from trades people, as to whether either one of these systems would be something they'd want to use (and would be helpful). I also want to hear from those who have no intention of being tradesfolk... I want to know if you would have any problems with essentially paying for other's trade skills (though these skills will benefit you as well, through armor, weapons and when it's added, spellcraft, as well as siegecraft). <br>
<br>
 <p>Haemish MacLennan<br>
